--- title: Chlorophyll Bottle Data --- ## Chlorophyll Data This is an example heat map to summarise chlorophyll data by month/year. ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} suppressMessages({ library(dplyr) library(ggplot2) }) # SQL query - Only grab bottle chlorophyll sql <- readLines("../../../static/sql/bottle.sql", n = 164) |> paste(collapse = "\n") sql <- paste(sql, "and lr.analyte = 'ChlorophyllA'") ## create connection to database con <- DBI::dbConnect( drv = RPostgres::Postgres(), dbname = Sys.getenv("POSTGRES_DATABASE"), host = Sys.getenv("POSTGRES_HOST"), port = Sys.getenv("POSTGRES_PORT"), user = Sys.getenv("POSTGRES_USER"), password = Sys.getenv("POSTGRES_PASSWORD") ) # query db bottle_data <- DBI::dbGetQuery(con, sql) DBI::dbDisconnect(con) # Create summary grouping <- c("year", "month", "analyte", "units") data_summary <- bottle_data |> mutate( year = lubridate::year(sample_date), month = lubridate::month(sample_date) ) |> summarise( .by = all_of(grouping), n = n(), q25 = quantile(result, 0.25, na.rm = TRUE), median = quantile(result, 0.5, na.rm = TRUE), q75 = quantile(result, 0.75, na.rm = TRUE) ) |> mutate( abb_month = month.abb[month], sum_date = as.Date(glue::glue("{year}-{month}-01")) ) |> arrange(year, month) fill_missing_data <- function(df) { # full set of years and months MONTH_YEAR <- unique(paste(df$year, "-", df$month)) missing_data <- expand.grid( year = seq(min(df$year), max(df$year), by = 1), month = 1:12 ) |> mutate(month_year = paste(year, "-", month)) |> filter(!month_year %in% MONTH_YEAR) bind_rows(df, missing_data) } hm_d <- data_summary |> fill_missing_data() |> mutate( across(c(q25, median, q75), ~signif(x = .x, digits = 3)), abb_month = month.abb[month], abb_month = factor(abb_month, levels = month.abb), tooltip = glue::glue( "{abb_month} {year}", "Count: {format(n, big.mark = ',')}", "25th: {q25} {units}", "Median: {median} {units}", "75th: {q75} {units}", .sep = "
", .na = "--" ) ) # Create Heat Map p <- ggplot(data = hm_d, aes(x = abb_month, y = year, fill = median)) + #geom_tile(color = "black", width = 1) + ggiraph::geom_tile_interactive(aes(tooltip = tooltip), color = "black", width = 1) + scale_fill_distiller( palette = "Greens", direction = 1, na.value = "gray90" ) + #coord_fixed() + # keep tile as square scale_x_discrete(expand = c(0,0), position = "top") + scale_y_reverse(expand = c(0,0)) + labs(ylab = "Year", fill = "Median Chlorophyll (ug/L)") + theme_bw() + theme( axis.title.x=element_blank(), panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), legend.position = "bottom" ) ggiraph::girafe(ggobj = p) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
